@startuml SabaGroupBetting_AssociationDetection
!theme plain
title Match Monitor Saba Group Betting - Simplified Association Detection (Updated 2025-11-19)

start

floating note left
    **COMPARISON: Standard vs Saba**
    
    Standard Group Betting:
    - Sport-specific configuration
    - 5 detection criteria (conditional)
    - Complex setup
    
    Saba Group Betting:
    - No configuration needed
    - 4 detection criteria (always ON)
    - Simple setup
end note

:Standard Group Betting
Configuration;

note right
    **Sport-Specific Settings:**
    - DeviceSports: "1,2,3,4,5"
    - AISports: "1,2,3,4,5"
    - IPSports: "1,2,3,4,5"
    - 3MatchesLast7DaysSports: "1,2,3,4,5"
    - IPLast3DaysSports: "1,2,3,4,5"
    
    **Dynamic Enabling:**
    IsDevice = DeviceSports.Contains(SportType)
    IsAI = AISports.Contains(SportType)
    IsIP = IPSports.Contains(SportType)
    
    **Result:** Different criteria per sport
    
    **5 Criteria:**
    ✓ Device (sport-specific)
    ✓ AI (sport-specific)
    ✓ IP (sport-specific)
    ✓ 3 Matches Last 7 Days (sport-specific)
    ✓ IP Last 3 Days (sport-specific)
end note

:Saba Group Betting
Configuration;

note right
    **Fixed Settings:**
    NO sport-specific configuration!
    
    **Always Enabled:**
    IsDevice = true
    IsAI = true
    IsIP = true
    Is3MatchesLast7Days = true
    
    **Result:** Same criteria for all matches
    
    **4 Criteria:**
    ✓ Device Detection (always ON)
    ✓ AI Detection (always ON)
    ✓ IP Detection (always ON)
    ✓ 3 Matches Last 7 Days (always ON)
    ✗ IP Last 3 Days (not used)
    
    **Saba-Specific:**
    + MappingCustDictionary required
end note

:Get Customer Lists;

note right
    From MatchStaging:
    - CTSCustIDList: "5001,5002,5003,5004"
    - CustIDList: "101,102,103,104"
    
    These are already mapped in staging
end note

:Create DetectAssociationParamModel;

note right
    **Saba Code (Simple):**
    
    var param = new DetectAssociationParamModel
    {
        CTSCustIds = ctsCustIDList,
        CustIds = custIDList,
        IsDevice = true,           // Always
        IsAI = true,               // Always
        IsIP = true,               // Always
        Is3MatchesLast7Days = true, // Always
        MappingCustDictionary = MappingCustDictionary
    };
    
    **Standard Code (Complex):**
    
    var param = new DetectAssociationParamModel
    {
        CTSCustIds = ctsCustIDList,
        CustIds = custIDList,
        IsDevice = AssDetectSetting.DeviceSports.Contains(sportType),
        IsAI = AssDetectSetting.AISports.Contains(sportType),
        IsIP = AssDetectSetting.IPSports.Contains(sportType),
        Is3MatchesLast7Days = 
            AssDetectSetting._3MatchesLast7DaysSports.Contains(sportType),
        IsIPLast3Days = 
            AssDetectSetting.IPLast3DaysSports.Contains(sportType),
        CustIdsIPLast3Days = licCustIDList
    };
end note

:Call AssociationDetectionService;

partition "Detection Processing (4 Criteria)" {
    
    :1. Device Detection (Always);
    note right
        Query CTSCustomer for DeviceID:
        SELECT CustID, DeviceID
        FROM CTSCustomer
        WHERE CTSCustID IN (5001, 5002, 5003, 5004)
        GROUP BY DeviceID
        HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
        
        Result: DeviceID "ABC123": [5001, 5002, 5003]
    end note
    
    :2. AI Detection (Always);
    note right
        Call AI/ML Service:
        - Analyze betting patterns
        - Calculate similarity scores
        - Group similar customers
        
        Result: Pattern Similarity: [5002, 5004]
    end note
    
    :3. IP Detection (Always);
    note right
        Query TicketTrans for IP:
        SELECT CustID, IPAddress
        FROM TicketTrans
        WHERE CTSCustID IN (5001, 5002, 5003, 5004)
            AND BetTime >= NOW() - INTERVAL 1 DAY
        GROUP BY IPAddress
        HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT CTSCustID) > 1
        
        Result: IP "192.168.1.100": [5001, 5002]
    end note
    
    :4. 3 Matches Last 7 Days (Always);
    note right
        Query co-betting history:
        SELECT CTSCustID1, CTSCustID2, COUNT(*) as MatchCount
        FROM (
            SELECT DISTINCT MatchID, CTSCustID
            FROM TicketTrans
            WHERE CTSCustID IN (5001, 5002, 5003, 5004)
                AND BetTime >= NOW() - INTERVAL 7 DAY
        ) t1
        JOIN t2 ON t1.MatchID = t2.MatchID
        GROUP BY CTSCustID1, CTSCustID2
        HAVING COUNT(*) >= 3
        
        Result: Co-bet 3+ times: [5001, 5002, 5003]
    end note
    
    :Merge All Detection Results;
    note right
        **Merge Logic:**
        1. Union all groups from 4 criteria
        2. If any overlap then Merge into one group
        3. Transitive grouping
        
        Example:
        - Device: {5001, 5002, 5003}
        - IP: {5001, 5002}
        - 3Matches: {5002, 5003}
        Merged: {5001, 5002, 5003} to GroupID 1
        
        - AI: {5004}
        Separate: {5004} to No GroupID (alone)
    end note
    
    :Assign GroupID and Type;
    note right
        For each group:
        - Assign sequential GroupID
        - Record which criteria detected it
        
        Example:
        {
            CTSCustID: 5001,
            GroupID: 1,
            AssociationType: "Device,IP,3Matches"
        }
    end note
}

:Filter: GroupID != null;

:Return Association Results;
note right
    IEnumerable<DetectAssociationMergeGroupEntity>
    
    Example:
    [
        { CTSCustID: 5001, GroupID: 1, Type: "Device,IP,3Matches" },
        { CTSCustID: 5002, GroupID: 1, Type: "Device,IP,3Matches" },
        { CTSCustID: 5003, GroupID: 1, Type: "Device,3Matches" }
    ]
    
    Customer 5004 not returned (no group)
end note

stop

floating note right
    ===========================================
    SABA ASSOCIATION DETECTION SUMMARY
    ===========================================
    
    **Simplifications:**
    ✅ No sport-specific configuration
    ✅ All criteria always enabled
    ✅ No IPLast3Days complexity
    ✅ No LicCustList needed
    ✅ Simpler code (~8 lines vs ~15 lines)
    
    **Saba-Specific:**
    🔧 MappingCustDictionary required
    🔧 Fixed criteria (4 instead of 5)
    
    **Same Detection Power:**
    - Device, AI, IP, 3Matches all work
    - Same grouping algorithm
    - Same accuracy
    
    **Benefits:**
    - Easier to maintain
    - Less configuration
    - Faster execution (no sport checks)
    - More predictable results
    
    **Trade-off:**
    - Less flexible
    - Cannot disable criteria per sport
    - Always runs all 4 detections
    
    **Use Case:**
    Perfect for Saba platform where:
    - All matches need same detection
    - No sport-specific requirements
    - Consistency over flexibility
end note

@enduml

